"Description":
I am often asked how I got the name Mugzy. Why of course, because of my awfully cute mug! I am a pretty strong brindle American Staffordshire so when you walk me, feel free to remind me gently of my manners and correct me if I pull. A tasty bit of cheese or hot dog would be a very welcome treat to help me in polishing up my manners! I am ok with other dogs. Given a choice between playing with toys or your affection, I will almost always choose your affection. After all, I can play with toys anytime, right?
Stop by and say hi!
Don''t forget to watch my video.

Do you like to play? I do! Since I went to a foster home, I have discovered that I LOVE toys! My foster family has had a lot of fun learning about me and my toy obsession. They say I''m housetrained, know my basic commands and enjoy being with people. I can''t wait to meet you and show off all my other fabulous qualities. My foster home is great, but what I really want is a forever home. Please contact my fosters if you want to know more about me … or if you want to bring me a toy!

"Description":
• Violet is a smart girl who knows numerous commands including `sit`, `stay`, `roll over`, `up`, and `shake”.
• Violet has good house manners and likes to ride in the car.
• Violet has participated in structured pack walks at the shelter, but can not participate in off-leash play groups.
• Due to her high prey drive, Violet can not live with cats or smaller dogs.
• Violet is very agile/athletic and was comfortable on all of the equipment in Canine Confidence classes.
• Violet''s friendly, loving personality make her a volunteer favorite.

Violet A545887 is one of many dogs who has received obedience training during her stay at VCAS. This happy girl knows several commands and was proud to show them off. Come on up to VCAS in Camarillo and meet Violet! She''s already spayed and ready to go home with you ASAP!

My name is Babs, I have been living with a foster family and I am ready to find my forever home now! Babs was pulled from the shelter with her two kittens and placed in a loving foster home until her kittens were old enough to be weaned and adopted.  This is a kitty that just wants to be loved. She is low energy and would be perfectly happy lying in your lap all day. Babs loves being petted and loved on. She is extremely sweet and affectionate. She can be a bit shy at first, but once she warms up to you she is a real doll. She may be low energy but she still has quite a bit of spunk in her and loves to play with feathers! Babs would be a great fit for most families, or even a single person looking for a companion. She would probably do best in a home with older children as she is low energy and can be shy at times. Babs would love to come home and snuggle on the end of your bed and keep your feet warm! Babs is currently available for adoption at Pet Smart in Oxnard - 2021 N Oxnard Blvd.

Ain''t no party like wiggle butt party cuz a wiggle butt party don''t stop. This happy little wiggle butt is Alize. She makes you warm and bubbly inside when she smiles at you. She warms up quickly, and within 24 hours she will be kissing your face and in your lap. She is fairly new to VCAS Camarillo, and has been overlooked because she is polite and not an in-your-face-puppy kind of dog. She is such a treasure, and probably has one of the coolest names ever to boot.

If you''ve been looking for a fun-loving, happy-go-lucky guy, I''m your man. I''m the marvelous, magnificent Max and my foster family has so many great things to say about me that they won''t all fit here, but contact them and they''ll answer any question you have. They''ll probably tell you I''m great with people and very sweet and loving. I''m housetrained, know some basic commands and am eager to please. If you have other pets and want to see how we might get along, my fosters can arrange a meeting. I''m so thankful to my foster family for getting me ready for a forever home, but I''m ready to take the next step. Let''s make each other''s dreams come true!

HARLEY (A612227) has energy, but keeps it under control. He has excellent manners; he doesn''t pull on the leash, takes treats very gently from your hand, and doesn''t jump up on people. He keeps all his wiggles planted nicely on the floor. This is a very balanced boy is a people pleaser. He does very well with other dogs and has fun in our doggy play groups. Come and meet him so he can show you how well he knows ''sit'' ''down'' and ''shake.''

• Emma is an energetic, friendly, and happy girl.

• Emma knows several commands, including `sit`, `speak`, `down`, and `leave it”.

• She loves to play, especially chasing tennis balls and playing tug.

• Emma pulls on her leash, but is working on her leash manners.

• Emma needs additional training, exercise, and guidance to curb her enthusiasm.

#vcaspitcrew

Greetings, my name is Mr. Darcy, and like my namesake I am very handsome and sophisticated, but I won’t be prideful or prejudiced of the family who chooses to adopt me! Please come and meet me if you would like a dashing and loyal companion!
Hobbies: relaxing with a good back massage and treat.
My perfect match: Anyone who would love to have a dashing gentleman in their life.

* Crate Trained
* House Trained
* Loves car rides
* Doesn''t get on furniture
* Quiet and mellow
* Great office dog!
* Goes home with a staff member every night - lives with an older female dog
* Enjoys tennis balls and rope toys

You might think with a name like Rambo, I would be a tough guy. You would be wrong! Oh sure, I''m young ( 2), energetic and somewhat of a clown. I admit it, I like people. I like them to walk me and I like them to play with toys with me. I get very enthusiastic when volunteers take me out of my kennel, and I sometimes forget my manners and jump up on them to give them a kiss. But, once you leash me up and get me outside, I am a marshmellow. I walk great on a leash, I make eye contact with my handler and I am fine with other dogs. I even know ''sit'' and ''down'' and am anxious to learn whatever else you want to teach me.
If you want to meet me and learn more about whether we would be the perfect match, go to the front office and ask them to show me to you. I can''t wait!

Daisy, Daisy give me your answer do, I am half crazy for the love of you!  That song was written just for me, I''m sure, and just like the song I am a winner!  I am a high energy, social girl who could benefit from a short refresher course reminding me of my manners. Sometimes I get so excited that I forget my manners and greet people by jumping up on them. But, I only do that because I want cuddles and attention from you. Who doesn''t want that? If you are a person who can appreciate my enthusiasm and willingness to learn, I am sure we will be perfect together.

• Sienna is a playful, energetic, and friendly girl.

• She knows the command `sit`, and is working on her leash manners.

• Sienna has not gotten along well with other dogs at the shelter, so we recommend that she be the only dog in her new home.

Hi, my shelter friends call me Voltaire and I haven''t been here very long, but it seems like a nice place. The food is good, my new friends chat with me and pet me when ever they can, and they give me nice plankets to keep me comfy in my kennel. What I''d really like though is a forever home and family to call my own. Once the shelter workers have a chance to get to know me better, they''ll have more to say about me. If you want to meet me right now though, that would be GREAT! The nice people at the Adoption center can arrange for us to meet today! Just take my kennel number with you and we can hang out for a bit.
Watch Voltaire''s video:

Mochi is an inquisitive young male who gets along with other cats and kittens as well as being by himself. He is a little temperamental. He wants to play, have fun, and then just relax. If you''re looking for a someone to lay on your lap or the need to be constantly entertained and give constant cuddles than keep looking. He is a round/robust male who needs to run, play and use his wrestling skills. Will you be up for the task? He likes neck, head and cheek scratches, but does not want to be picked up or held.

Laser pointers are his friend. Shoe strings, cat toys, mice, oh he loves them all. When you''ve exhausted his energy and it''s time for bed, you''ll be rewarded with his softer quieter side. If you''re interested in adopting this young cat, contact his foster Mom: sultana.humera@gmail.com

Once upon a time I was a handsome pup with my life before me. But, life hasn''t always been easy for me and, through no fault of my own, I ended up here at VCAS. But, I am not going to let being here keep me down. I am in good spirits because I keep thinking that a nice, loving human is going to adopt me and we are going to be happy furever after. Like many men of advanced years, my fur is thinning, but I am ok with that. I have very nice manners, I know `sit` and `shake` and I am a treat hound! I love to play fetch and when I see grass, watch out because I love to roll in it! I am hoping that someone who likes massages will adopt me because massages are one of my most favorite things in the whole world! The volunteers here at VCAS are very good at giving me massages.
But, most of all, just like you, I just want a human of my own to love and who will shower me with as much love as they have to give!

* Good on leash
* Non-reactive to dogs. PackWalk participant
* Lower energy dog with good house manners
* Crate and house trained
* Knows `sit`, `down` and `shake` commands
* Lived with cats while in foster care

Ready for 80 pounds of pure love? If so, then you must meet me: I''m Duke and I am your dream dog! My foster family says I''m very sweet and easygoing. I have a great time meeting new people and other dogs on my daily walks, and I am very social and affectionate. I know my basic commands and I''m even crate-trained. Right now I''m living with some cats and I have a canine buddy, but if you have pets and want to see how we might get along, my fosters can arrange a meeting. But first you might want to get a new dog bed, some bowls and other supplies because once you meet me you won''t let me go!

My name is Olive, also known as “Queen of Binkies” around the bunny barn. My foster mom was very impressed with how low-maintenance I am. I am super tidy and always use my litter box. Even when I get playtime out of my x-pen I still go back to my litter box to potty. My favorite hobbies are playing under blankets, eating banana, zoomies around the room, and I LOVE to binky when I get out of my x-pen. In fact, I am almost an entirely different bunny when I get out and can stretch my legs and roam around. I require only some supervision outside of my x-pen and never nibbled too much on wood furniture or cords (I am still a bunny after all and shouldn’t be trusted since we all love to nibble on stuff we shouldn’t!). I get a little restless in my x-pen and a little uncomfortable sharing a small space with someone else, but with patience I may change my attitude someday. I am not a morning bunny and I sleep most of the day (but dried cranberries and banana always perks me up), but late afternoon and nighttime is when I come alive, and when I like to be pet and held the most. I would do best in a house without small children, and with adults who are patient with my behavioral quirks but willing to work on them. With the right people I know I could change my attitude, I just hate being at the shelter where I don’t get a lot of attention. My foster mom thinks I have great potential for being a very fun and entertaining pet and I’m looking forward to finding my forever family soon!

• Leon is a strong, friendly, happy dog.

• He is working on his leash manners.

• Leon loves to play fetch.

* Friendly 2 year old dog with moderate energy
* Housebroken and good house manners
* Friendly to strangers and children according to her prior owner
* Engaging, likes giving kisses and tummy rubs
* Knows the commands `sit` and `down`
* Playful. Enjoys tennis balls, tug toys and chase

Greetings, furriends! I normally sleep all day, but I woke up for a few minutes so I could write something about myself because I''m hoping it might help me find a home. My buddies at the shelter want you to know I''m a very nice kitty who is low-maintenance and self-cleaning (yay! I''m drought-friendly!). I love to just lounge around and watch the world go by. If you are looking for an awesome cat who will keep you company when you need it but also let you do your own thing when you want to, come pick me up today and you will not be disappointed. Whew, writing this little blurb has me all tuckered out! OK, back to my Zzzzz....

• Mack''s previous owner reported that he is sometimes nervous in new situations, but warms up quickly.

• His previous owner also reported that Mack is good with kids.

Zeus is an active and energetic 3 year old boy who loves toys and a good game of fetch. He enjoys getting affection and a good scratch behind the ears. Because he is treat motivated and responsive to his handler, Zeus will make a loving and playful pet. He''d make a great jogging or hiking partner.

* Zeus is a friendly dog with a moderate to moderately high energy level
* He knows the commands `sit`, `shake` and `down`
* Zeus is playful. Loves playing fetch
* He''s participated in large dog playgroups
* Not recommended with younger children or small animals

Ranger has been lucky enough to get to take a litte vacation in foster and has done very well!!  He spends time with other dogs, is house trained, and enjoys relaxing in a home.  He is currently at our Simi Valley shelter, where you can meet him or contact vcar.foster@ventura.org for more information!

My name is Jordan and I am one of the sweetest cats you will ever meet! I would love for you to come visit me in my kennel, where I will rub up against the bars in an attempt to get some pets from you. I am very gentle and would love to go to a home where I can sleep in your lap for as long as I want. Please come take me home today!

Hi, I''m Billie Jean, and as you can see, I am a voluptuous Chihuahua who was named after the famous tennis player. Just like her, I once played with a tennis ball!
Snuggling under mounds of warm and cozy blankets is one of the talents at which I excel. Like many seniors, I am a little slow to rise in the morning, and if rushed, I can get a little grumpy. My idea of a perfect start to each day is for you to wake me gently and slowly, and while I stretch and slowly come to, you fetch me some coffee in my favorite dainty cup. Just place it by my bedside, please and i will sip it at my leisure. Once I get out of bed, I am a very happy gal who will be anxious to sample the breakfast you have lovingly prepared for me. After breakfast, we can go for a walk or we can take a nap. You choose.
I like to be around other small dogs and have shared kennel space with a few. We have always gotten along fine and, if I feel the need to have my own space, I simply climb in bed and pull the covers around me!
I would be so grateful to spend what time I have left in a warm home with people to love and adore me. A nice bed with lots of blankets would also have to be part of the deal!

Just as my name indicates, I am the sweetest cat ever! I am like a little old lady who loves to sip tea and knit while watching `Golden Girls` reruns. If you pet me, I will purr like an 1978 Chevy Chevelle motor. My friends at the shelter tell me I am so deserving of a loving home where I can stretch out and take naps in the sunshine. Please come meet me and see for yourself what an adorable little granny I am!

Look into my eyes... aren''t they beautiful? I''m Jake and I''m the most adorable boy you will ever meet. I love all people and if you visit my kennel, I have my very own brush you can use to groom me (and I will even purr for you!). I have diabetes but I don''t think that should disqualify me from a loving home, do you? My condition is totally manageable and our vet office can show you how to administer my medication. If you''ve been looking for a hunk of fluffy goodness, look no further: I''m your man!

Eddie likes to take walks, so much that sometimes he can pull a little until he gets going and settles down. He will thrive in a calm, adult home where he can get all the attention and many butt scratches!

If you are looking for a calm companion to take on your daily long walks, Eddie may just be your man!

* Smart. Knows sit, down, shake, heel, back, high 5 and wait
* Treat motivated
* Loves affection
* Playgroup participant. Described as selective
* Housebroken according to his prior owner
* Good hiking or jogging partner
* Mellow, but playful
* Needs help with his leash manners

Have you been wanting a sweet, calm, calico cat to make your life complete? Well, that would be my calling. I am a beautiful girl who adores people and treats. Mmmm... treats... My former owner had to give me up because she moved to a place that wouldn''t allow me to live with her. But she reports that I am a loving, mellow kitty who has lived happily with other cats before. I''ve enjoyed making new fur friends here at the Kitty Cottage in the shelter. But I really miss having a home of my own--won''t you please share yours with me?

Aspen is enjoying her shelter break in her foster home, but would really prefer to have a forever family to call her own. Clearly she enjoys other dogs as we have three dachshunds, and she just loves to soak up the sun.

We had a blast at the Ventura St. Patrick''s Day Parade, and made quite an impression on the audience who loved her hat.

What we have learned about her is that she is very easy to please. Short walks, soft bedding, and as much food as possible are her favorite things. She has a bit of arthritis but it does not stop her from engaging in a full lope to get back home.

Aspen talks sometimes and will freely give kisses when you stroke her head. She sleeps in her kennel at night and uses it for her four or five catnaps in the day. Because she is about ten years old, she sometimes has to go out to go potty in the night. She will verbally communicate this as she can be quite chatty...not barking chatty though.

Lastly, balls seem to get her pretty excited. Have not figured out if she wants to play or destroy...poor foursquare ball.

Aspen has a very compelling back story which includes having served as a blood donor dog in a vet''s office for many years. Please contact the shelter or my cell if you have any further questions, and if your heart is as big as Aspen''s.

My number is 805 279-2999
